reporter-output.line: STEP 1
Open url 'http://install.qa5.nbcupublisher7.publisher7.com'.
Enter 'admin@publisher.nbcuni.com' in the 'Email Address' text box.
Enter 'pa55word' in the 'Password' text box.
Click the 'Login' button.
STEP 2
Click the 'Modules' menu link.
Switch to the active frame titled 'Modules dialog'.
Enter 'TVE Adobe Pass' in the 'Filter Name' text box.
Wait for the module titled 'TVE Adobe Pass' to appear in the list.
Check the 'TVE Adobe Pass' check box.
Click the 'Save configuration' button.
Switch to frame titled 'Some required modules must be enabled'.
Click the 'Continue' button to enable additional modules.
Switch back to the 'Modules' frame.
Switch to frame titled 'Modules'.
Verify success message of 'The configuration options have been saved.' is present.
Enter 'TVE Auth Example' in the 'Filter Name' text box.
Wait for the module titled 'TVE Auth Example' to appear in the list.
Check the 'TVE Auth Example' check box.
Click the 'Save configuration' button.
Switch to frame titled 'Some required modules must be enabled'.
Click the 'Continue' button to enable additional modules.
Switch back to the 'Modules' frame.
Switch to frame titled 'Modules'.
Verify success message of 'The configuration options have been saved.' is present.
Enter 'TVE MVPD' in the 'Filter Name' text box.
Wait for the module titled 'TVE MVPD' to appear in the list.
Verify the 'TVE MVPD' check box is checked.
Click the 'Close Overlay X'.
STEP 3
Mouse over the 'Structure' menu link.
Click the 'Blocks' menu link.
Switch to the active frame titled 'Blocks dialog'.
Select the block name 'TVE Auth Example' from the 'Sidebar first' drop down list.
Click the 'Save Blocks' button.
Verify success message of 'The block settings have been updated.' is present.
Click the 'Close Overlay X'.
STEP 4
Verify the text 'The MVPD Connection must be setup.' is present on the page.
Verify the text 'The Adobe Pass configuration must be setup.' is present on the page.
Verify the text 'Configure jQuery to use version 1.7 or higher.' is present on the page.
STEP 5
Click the 'setup' link for MVPD Connection.
Switch to the active frame titled 'MVPD dialog'.
Enter 'http://mvpd-admin.nbcuni.com/mvpd/service' in the 'MVPD Service URL' text box.
Enter 'Syfy' in the 'Requestor ID' text box.
Select 'stage' from the 'Instance' drop down list.
Enter 'Oops! Something went wrong while fetching providers!' in the 'Generic Error Message' text area.
Click the 'Save configuration' button.
Verify success message of 'The configuration options have been saved.' is present.
Click the 'Close Overlay X'.
STEP 6
Verify the text 'The MVPD Connection must be setup.' is NOT present on the page.
STEP 7
Click the 'setup' link for Adobe Pass configuration.
Switch to the active frame titled 'Adobe Pass dialog'.
Enter 'http://entitlement.auth-staging.adobe.com/entitlement/AccessEnablerDebug.swf' in the 'Access Enabler Location' text box.
Enter '30000' in the 'Request Timeout' text box.
Enter '10.1.13' in the 'Adobe Flash Version' text box.
Enter 'syfy' in the 'Requestor ID' text box.
Enter 'syfy' in the 'Resource ID' text box.
Enter 'Your TV subscription does not include this channel. Please contact your TV Provider about upgrading your service to get access.' in the 'User not Authorized Error' text box.
Enter 'We had a problem reaching your TV provider. Please try again.' in the 'Internal Authorization Error' text box.
Enter 'Your TV subscription does not include this channel.' in the 'Generic Authorization Error' text box.
Enter 'http://api.auth-staging.adobe.com/api/v1/config/' in the 'Adobe Pass Config Service Path' text box.
Click the 'Test configuration' button.
Verify success message of 'All the configurations are valid.' is present.
STEP 8
Enter 'syfy' in the 'Requestor ID' text box.
Enter 'syfy' in the 'Resource ID' text box.
Click the 'Save configuration' button.
Verify success message of 'The configuration options have been saved.' is present.
Click the 'Close Overlay X'.
STEP 9
Verify the text 'The Adobe Pass configuration must be setup.' is NOT present on the page.
STEP 10
Click the 'Configure jQuery' link.
Switch to the active frame titled 'jQuery update dialog'.
Select '1.7' from the 'Default jQuery Version' drop down list.
Click the 'Save configuration' button.
Verify success message of 'The configuration options have been saved.' is present.
Click the 'Close Overlay X'.
STEP 11
Verify the 'Authentication status checked:' value is 'true'.
Verify the 'Authenticated' value is 'false'.
Verify the 'Selected MVPD:' value is 'none'.
STEP 12
Select 'Optimum' from the 'Al VMPDs:' drop down list.
Click the 'login' button.
Enter 'research40' in the 'Optimum ID' text box.
Enter 'support40' in the 'Password' text box.
Click the 'SIGN IN' button.
Verify the 'Authentication status checked:' value is 'true'.
Verify the 'Authenticated' value is 'true'.
Verify the 'Selected MVPD:' value is 'Cablevision'.
CLEANUP
Mouse over the 'Structure' menu link.
Click the 'Blocks' menu link.
Switch to the active frame titled 'Blocks dialog'.
Select the block name 'TVE Auth Example' from the '- None -' drop down list.
Click the 'Save Blocks' button.
Open url 'http://install.qa5.nbcupublisher7.publisher7.com/#overlay=admin/config/development/jquery_update'.
Switch to the active frame titled 'jQuery update dialog'.
Select '1.5' from the 'Default jQuery Version' drop down list.
Click the 'Save configuration' button.
